SIMPLE: deficiency
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Deficiency
<hw>De*fi"cien*cy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Deficiencies</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[See
<er>Deficient</er>.]</ety> <def>The state of being deficient;
inadequacy; want; failure; imperfection; shortcoming; defect.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧A <xex>deficiency</xex> of blood.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Arbuthnot.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>[Marlborough] was so miserably ignorant, that his
<qex>deficiencies</qex> made him the ridicule of his contemporaries.</q>
<rj><qau>Buckle.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Deficiency of a curve</b></col> <fld>(Geom.)</fld>,
<cd>the amount by which the number of double points on a curve is short
of the maximum for curves of the same degree.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Deficient</ent>⟦br⟧
